consensus text: A friend who travelled into Sicily in the year
1803 has favoured me with a perusal of his
They were written with no other [deletion]view[/deletion] view
than that of recalling to his memory scenes that
had strongly impressed him at the moment
I know that his descriptions are just and they
are so vivid that I am sure I need make no
apology for introducing them in illustration
In speaking of the lower part of Etna He
says the ascent at first is not very difficult
Fields of exuberant fertility smile on [deletion]every[/deletion] every
The coffee plant and saffron all grow here
